Sec. 201.011. COMPOSITION. The State Soil and Water
Conservation Board is a state agency composed of seven members as
follows:
(1) one member elected from each of the state districts in
accordance with this subchapter; and
(2) two members appointed by the governor, each of whom is:
(A) actively engaged in the business of farming, animal
husbandry, or other business related to agriculture and who wholly or
partly owns or leases land used in connection with that business;
and
(B) not a member of the board of directors of a
conservation district.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1461, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.
Amended by Acts 2003, 78th Leg., ch. 200, Sec. 13(a), eff. Sept. 1,
2003; Acts 2003, 78th Leg., ch. 983, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 2003.

